dataIdInfo.idAbs:
Ward shape file (polygons) for Myanmar which includes 236 towns. Source: Digitization based General Administration Department (GAD) Township profile maps 2018, except for Sagaing, Kengtung, Taungoo and Hpa-An cities based on field sources.

P-codes missing in Kyaikto (Mon): 1 ward.

This dataset was mainly digitized at 1:250,000 scale. Place names are in line with the general cartographic practice to reflect the names of such places as designated by the host governments. The information contained on this product is provided “as is”, for reference purposes only, based on current available information. The United Nations and the MIMU specifically do not make any warranties or representations as to the accuracy or completeness of such information nor does it imply official endorsement or acceptance by the United Nations. Please share any errors or omissions via maps@themimu.info.

dataLineage.statement:
Layer was downloaded by ITOS from HDX. It was then analyzed by ITOS for errors. Those errors were kept as-is and then the layer was sent back to UNOCHA as a feature class within a file geodatabase.
The following was found by ITOS: 1. 39 gap errors and 37 overlap errors were found. 2. 15 nesting errors exist among layers. 3. Admin5 pcodes do not build off of Admin2 p-codes. 4. 35 Admin5 p-codes are blank. 28 Admin5 names are blank. One record has blank Admin5 attribution and blank geometry. 5. 8 multipart sliver errors exist. 6. 24 Admin5 English and Burmese names do not have a 1 to 1 relationship. 7. Admin5 has 4 duplicated p-codes: "(blank)", "MMR013023701504" is used for 17 features, "MMR005011701503" and "MMR013029701504". 8. 6 Admin5 units named "Industrial Zone" exist in Admin4 "Dagon Myothit (Seikkan)". 2 Admin5 units named "Ma Har Myaing Ward" exist in Admin4 "Taze Town". They have the same p-code. 2 Admin5 units named "Taung Bet Paing Ward" exist in Admin4 "Kungyangon Town". They have the same p-code.
